text: The St. Mary of the Sea College (Spanish: Colegio Santa María del Mar) is a Jesuit college in A Coruña, Spain, founded in 1964, and covers infant through baccalaureate. Miguel Fisac designed the building to have an unobstructed view of the sea. The College's football U16 team came in first among 32 teams, advancing to the intercontinental final in Austria. ==References== Category:Jesuit secondary schools in Spain Category:Catholic schools in Spain Category:Secondary schools in Spain Category:Jesuit secondary schools Category:Educational institutions established in 1964
